HEADWORD: Smaltite
<hw>Smalt"ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Smalt</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A tin-white or gray mineral of metallic luster. It is an arsenide
of cobalt, nickel, and iron. Called also
<altname>speiskobalt</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

